The flour sold at this place as “teff” flour produced in “Africa” is NOT teff flour at all. The package is mischievously complete with a green, yellow, red lion’s logo to deceptively associate the hazardous item with Africa/Ethiopia. As if the mindless deception, which is hazardous to public health, weren’t bad enough, the false “teff flour” is sold for at least $10 more than the price at which a similar amount of a more genuine teff flour is sold elsewhere. I urge people of Ethiopian origin and other consumers of teff flour not to buy and use this particular product. I also hereby ask the store/restaurant to remove the product right away.
